This license covers nonna's own code (nonna/, editor/, tests/, spike/, docs).
The vendored engine (vendor/opengrep, a git submodule) is a separate work
licensed under LGPL-2.1; this repository distributes only a submodule pointer
to it. Binaries built from this repository statically link the LGPL-2.1
engine: LGPL §6 obligations are satisfied by the public availability of this
repository's source and build instructions, which allow relinking against a
modified version of the engine.
